cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.EC, cs.AI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the analysis of revenue maximization, which is a common topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.EC). The use of additive valuations suggests that the paper may involve combinatorial optimization (cs.DS) techniques. The discussion of extensions to multiple buyers and correlated valuations suggests that the paper may also involve topics related to multi-agent systems (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
